13|2013 Seanad abolition referendum]] reported in 2015 on proposed reforms, which included radical changes in the Seanad electoral system and the creation of a "Seanad Electoral Commission" to oversee this.<ref name="workgingroup2015"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taoiseach.gov.ie/eng/Work_Of_The_Department/Protocol/Working_Group_on_Seanad_Reform/Seanad_Bill_2015_.pdf#page=24|title=Part 8: Seanad Electoral Commission |author=Working Group on Seanad Reform |date=5 May 2015|work=Seanad Bill 2015 [draft] |publisher=Department of the Taoiseach|pages=24–25|accessdate=13 May 2015}}</ref> The working group's report recognised that the Electoral Commission already proposed by the government would, if established, make a separate Seanad Electoral Commission unnecessary.<ref name="workgingroup2015">{{cite web |url=http://www.taoiseach.gov.ie/eng/Work_Of_The_Department/Protocol/Working_Group_on_Seanad_Reform/2nd_version_Final_Seanad_Reform.pdf#page=36 |format=PDF |title=Report |publisher=Department of the Taoiseach |author=Working Group on Seanad Reform |date=April 2015 |page=37 |quote=The Working Group recognises that the Electoral Commission, to be established by the Government, would have responsibility far beyond Seanad Elections and in that regard that the Interim body and its functions would be subsumed into the wider Electoral Commission. |accessdate=13 May 2015}}</ref> |- | Policy, strategy, and research | Franchise Section | Oir | The Oireachtas report emphasises independent research. |- | Publication of results | Returning officers, Franchise Section | Oir | Returning officers publish summaries in ''[[Iris Oifigiúil]]'' shortly after the poll; the Department publishes detailed results later. The Oireachtas report addresses real-time official publication online. |- | Standards for [[electronic voting]] | N/A | | Recommended in 2005 by the Commission on Electronic Voting formed after [[Electronic voting in Ireland|the abortive 2003 e-voting trial]].<ref name="evoting